recalls.Summary: BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain model year 2013 528i, 528i xDrive, 535i, 535i xDrive, 550i, 550i xDrive, and ActiveHybrid 5 vehicles.  The rear reflex reflectors may not reflect enough light.  As such, the vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 108, "Lamps, Reflective Devices, and Associated Equipment."
recalls.Consequence: The vehicle may be less visible to other vehicles, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: BMW will notify owners, and dealers will replace the rear reflex reflectors, free of charge.  The recall began July 28, 2017.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

complaints.summary: My car (a 2014 BMW M5 with only approx. 39K miles) has a known issue with defective fuel injectors (manufactured by Bosch, subsequently replaced by an upgraded part). In fact, in 2018 BMW issued me and other owners with an extended warranty for the fuel injectors for 10 years/120,000 miles (see attached copy). However, in my opinion and based on a 9/7/2022 failure incident I experienced the defective fuel injectors should have resulted in a safety recall.  Previously, my car experienced a check engine light in August 2022.  The dealership suspected one or more leaking fuel injectors and noted as such on my repair invoice, but I was told due to the testing protocol which BMW requires they could not replace any of the fuel injectors. BMW's testing protocol also resulted in me incurring a large bill of almost $1,100 due to the diagnosis labor involved.  On 9/7/2022 while I was driving on the highway at approximately 70 miles an hour, 2 fuel injectors failed (out of 8 injectors, confirmed by subsequent repair) which resulted in a sudden and complete loss of engine power while maneuvering in traffic. I am extremely lucky the sudden loss of engine power did not result in an accident, and I was able to take a highway exit using the vehicle's momentum. Upon exiting the highway, my car's engine completely died and would not re-start. This resulted in my car obstructing the road where it almost caused several accidents and necessitated a 911 call by me to obtain police assistance to get my vehicle out of the way.  After this frightening experience and due to the high failure rate I already experienced with 2 out of 8 injectors, I contacted BMW customer service and attempted to get the remaining 6 injectors replaced. BMW refuses to replace the remaining injectors and stated they would only replace a specific injector after failure.  I urge the NHTSA to require BMW to perform a safety related recall for this known fuel injector issue.

BEHAVIOR OF MY CAR'S DCT TRANSMISSION HAS CREATED A DANGEROUS SITUATION WHICH ALMOST RESULTED IN AN ACCIDENT FOR ME. I BELIEVE THIS IS DUE TO A SOFTWARE CHANGE BMW MADE TO THE DCT TRANSMISSION. THE ISSUE IS AS FOLLOWS:    -WHEN DRIVING AT HIGHWAY SPEED, WHEN YOU RELEASE THE THROTTLE AND LET THE VEHICLE COAST (AS WHEN YOU WANT THE VEHICLE TO NATURALLY DECELERATE WITHOUT BRAKING) THE TRANSMISSION WILL DISENGAGE THE DCT CLUTCHES. THE CAR WILL THEN MAINTAIN SPEED (AS IF CRUISE CONTROL WERE ENGAGED) INSTEAD OF NATURALLY DECELERATING. IN AND OF ITSELF, THIS BEHAVIOR IS DANGEROUS DUE TO THE FACT THE VEHICLE WILL MAINTAIN UNWANTED SPEED.  -WHEN THEN TRYING TO RE-ACCELERATE QUICKLY FROM COASTING WHERE A DOWNSHIFT IS NEEDED (AS IN WHEN NEEDING TO PASS LEGALLY ON A 2 LANE HIGHWAY), THE CAR WILL NOT RE-ENGAGE THE CLUTCHES FOR A COUPLE OF SECONDS OR SO.  THIS CAUSES TOTAL LOSS OF POWER OR ACCELERATION FOR 2 OR SO SECONDS.    WHILE THIS MAY SEEM LIKE A RELATIVELY MINOR SITUATION, THE ABOVE SITUATION ALMOST CAUSED A SERIOUS ACCIDENT AT HIGHWAY SPEED. ALSO, MY CAR DID NOT PREVIOUSLY DISPLAY THIS BEHAVIOR UNTIL AFTER A SERVICE VISIT (I BELIEVE LAST YEAR). I SUSPECT THE DCT TRANSMISSION SOFTWARE WAS UPDATED BY BMW WITHOUT MY KNOWLEDGE AND IS THE SOURCE OF THIS CHANGE IN VEHICLE BEHAVIOR.

issues.title: Rod Bearing Failure
issues.description: The S63 engine in F10 M5 Competition models is prone to premature rod bearing wear and failure, which can lead to catastrophic engine damage. This is a well-documented issue affecting the twin-turbo V8 engine.
issues.fix_description: Complete engine rebuild or replacement, preventive rod bearing replacement with upgraded bearings
issues.prevention: Regular oil analysis, frequent oil changes with high-quality oil, avoid extended high RPM driving

issues.title: Turbocharger Wastegate Rattle
issues.description: The twin turbochargers develop wastegate actuator arm issues causing rattling noises and potential boost control problems. This affects performance and can lead to turbo failure.
issues.fix_description: Replace turbocharger wastegate actuators or complete turbocharger units
issues.prevention: Use high-quality fuel, regular maintenance, avoid excessive heat cycling

issues.title: High Pressure Fuel Pump (HPFP) Failure
issues.description: The high pressure fuel pump fails prematurely, causing fuel starvation issues and potential engine damage. This is a common problem across BMW's N63/S63 engine family.
issues.fix_description: Replace high pressure fuel pump with updated part number
issues.prevention: Use quality fuel, replace fuel filter regularly, avoid running on low fuel

issues.title: Carbon Buildup on Intake Valves
issues.description: Direct injection engines suffer from carbon buildup on intake valves due to lack of fuel washing over the valves, leading to reduced performance and rough running.
issues.fix_description: Walnut blasting or manual cleaning of intake valves and ports
issues.prevention: Regular highway driving, quality fuel with additives, periodic intake cleaning service

issues.title: Active Autowerke Active M Differential Failure
issues.description: The electronically controlled rear differential experiences pump failures and internal component wear, causing loss of differential function and potential safety issues.
issues.fix_description: Replace differential unit or rebuild with updated components
issues.prevention: Regular differential service, avoid excessive track use without proper cooling

issues.title: Cooling System Failures
issues.description: Various cooling system components fail prematurely including water pumps, thermostats, and coolant hoses, leading to overheating and potential engine damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace failed cooling system components, flush cooling system
issues.prevention: Regular coolant changes, inspect hoses and connections, monitor coolant levels

issues.title: DCT Transmission Clutch Pack Failure
issues.description: The 7-speed dual clutch transmission experiences premature clutch pack wear, especially in Competition models with increased power output.
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch packs and update transmission software
issues.prevention: Proper warm-up procedures, avoid aggressive launches when cold, regular transmission service

issues.title: Electronic Issues and Module Failures
issues.description: Various electronic control modules fail causing intermittent issues with vehicle systems including iDrive, climate control, and driver assistance features.
issues.fix_description: Replace or reprogram affected control modules
issues.prevention: Keep software updated, avoid aftermarket modifications to electrical system

issues.title: Suspension Component Wear
issues.description: Performance suspension components including bushings, ball joints, and control arms wear prematurely due to the high-performance nature and weight of the vehicle.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn suspension components with OEM or upgraded parts
issues.prevention: Avoid potholes and harsh impacts, regular suspension inspections

issues.title: Brake System Premature Wear
issues.description: High-performance brake components wear quickly under normal driving conditions, with brake pads and rotors requiring frequent replacement.
issues.fix_description: Replace brake pads and rotors with high-performance components
issues.prevention: Avoid aggressive braking, allow brakes to cool after spirited driving

editorial.tagline: The ultimate business express with supercar performance
editorial.hero_blurb: BMW's F10 M5 Competition represents the final evolution of the naturally-aspirated M5 era, delivering 575 horsepower through a masterful 4.4L twin-turbo V8. This is executive transport that can embarrass supercars while carrying four adults in luxury.
editorial.essence: The F10 M5 Competition strikes the perfect balance between sophisticated luxury sedan and track-capable performance machine. Its S63 engine delivers devastating power with remarkable refinement, making it the ideal sleeper for those who need both boardroom credibility and backroad dominance.
editorial.heritage: Continuing the M5 tradition since 1985, the F10 generation marked BMW's transition from naturally aspirated to forced induction while maintaining the core M5 philosophy of ultimate sports sedan performance. The Competition package represented the pinnacle of this generation's development.
editorial.design_philosophy: BMW M engineers focused on creating a wolf in sheep's clothing - aggressive performance wrapped in understated elegance. The Competition package added subtle visual cues and enhanced dynamics without sacrificing the M5's ability to blend into executive parking lots.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not directly race-bred, the F10 M5 drew heavily from BMW's motorsport expertise, particularly in turbo technology and chassis dynamics developed through their touring car and endurance racing programs.
editorial.engine_character: The S63 4.4L twin-turbo V8 delivers power with authority and sophistication, building torque from low RPMs with a surge that never seems to end. Despite the turbos, it maintains a naturally responsive character with minimal lag and linear power delivery.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 7-speed DCT fires off shifts with lightning precision, offering both smooth automatic operation for daily driving and razor-sharp manual control for spirited driving. Shifts are firm but never harsh in the context of the car's mission.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Remarkably composed for its size, the F10 M5 Competition can dance through corners with surprising agility while maintaining rock-solid stability at autobahn speeds. The adaptive suspension provides both comfort and cornering capability.
editorial.steering_feel: Electric power steering that manages to retain good feedback and weight, though not quite matching the hydraulic feel of earlier generations. Quick ratio provides sharp turn-in while remaining stable at speed.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive brakes provide fade-free stopping power with excellent modulation and feel. The pedal remains firm and progressive even under hard track use, instilling complete confidence in the car's stopping ability.
editorial.sound_signature: A sophisticated growl that builds to an authoritative roar under acceleration, with subtle turbo whistle adding complexity. The exhaust note is refined yet purposeful, never crude but unmistakably powerful.
editorial.ideal_owner: Successful professionals who need a single car that excels as both daily driver and weekend warrior. Perfect for those who appreciate understated performance and want supercar capability without the attention or compromises.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Pure track enthusiasts seeking the lightest, most focused experience, or those wanting maximum engagement over refinement. Also not ideal for buyers seeking maximum reliability or low running costs.
editorial.buyers_summary: Look for well-maintained examples with full service history, particularly rod bearing maintenance. The Competition package is worth seeking out for its enhanced dynamics and subtle visual upgrades that complete the F10 M5 experience.

expertReviews.title: The most Misunderstood BMW | F10 M5 Month 1 Owner Review
pros: DCT gearbox provides engaging manual-like driving experience
Hydraulic steering with excellent feel and feedback
Sweet spot of old-school involvement with modern torque
Great engine sound with proper V8 character
Decent fuel consumption (9-10 km/L highway, 5 km/L city)
More involving than newer M5s with ZF8 automatic
Active steering provides sharp turn-in for large car
cons: DCT automatic mode not intuitive, requires manual override
Reputation as widow maker in wet conditions
expertReviews.verdict: The F10 M5 represents a sweet spot in the M5 lineage, combining old-school driving involvement with modern performance. It features the engaging DCT gearbox that encourages manual control, hydraulic steering with excellent feedback, and a characterful V8 engine. While misunderstood due to its weight and early torque delivery reputation, it offers more driver engagement than newer automatic M5s. The reviewer sees it as potentially the most misunderstood car, not just M5, due to timing in the market before high-torque cars became common.

expertReviews.title: BMW F10 M5 Competition Review! | The Best M Car Value?
pros: S63 4.4L twin-turbo V8 with 575hp
Seven-speed dual clutch transmission
Carbon ceramic brakes
Executive package with full leather interior
Heads-up display and massaging seats
Sounds amazing without OPF filters
Functional M5 side vents
Quad exhaust tips
110k miles showing it's actually driven
cons: No Apple CarPlay or Android Auto
No rev limiter mentioned as potential concern
expertReviews.verdict: The 2014 BMW F10 M5 Competition showcases BMW's excellent S63 twin-turbo V8 engine producing 575hp, paired with a sophisticated dual-clutch transmission and premium executive package features. The reviewer emphasizes this as a well-used example with 110k miles, highlighting the car's impressive sound without modern OPF filters and comprehensive luxury features including carbon ceramic brakes and massaging seats.

expertReviews.title: BMW F10 M5 Competition Review | Best Value Hot Saloon ...
pros: Excellent ride height and factory setup that doesn't need modification
Very discreet appearance that blends in while hiding massive performance
More comfortable and confidence-inspiring than F80 M3 in same price range
Comprehensive Competition pack upgrades including quicker steering rack, firmer suspension, louder exhaust
Spacious and comfortable interior with excellent BMW steering wheel design
Strong braking performance with large cross-drilled discs
Flat-plane crank V8 with unique hot-V turbo configuration creates distinctive sound
cons: Potential carbon ceramic brake replacement costs of 10,000 make them risky on used cars
S63 engine based on problematic N63 platform - warranty recommended due to potential reliability issues
Dashboard architecture showing age compared to modern BMW interiors
Chrome M5 badge looks out of place with black exhaust tips on Competition pack
expertReviews.verdict: The F10 M5 Competition represents excellent value in the high-performance saloon segment, offering a substantial upgrade package over the standard car for 7,000 when new. With 575hp, discreet styling, and a more confidence-inspiring character than the F80 M3, it's the ultimate 'executive missile' that can blend into corporate car parks yet embarrass supercars. The reviewer emphasizes the importance of warranty coverage due to potential engine reliability issues, but praises the car's split personality between comfort and performance.

expertReviews.title: BMW F10 M5 Competition Package - One Take
pros: 630hp actual power output vs 600hp rated
Excellent dual-clutch transmission
Multiple driving modes from comfort cruiser to track beast
Impressive straight-line performance
High-quality interior materials
Seat massagers
Great highway refinement
cons: Very stiff ride quality even in comfort mode
Too much power can be overwhelming
expertReviews.verdict: The F10 M5 Competition is a proper performance machine that excels as both a comfortable highway cruiser and a serious performance car. With underrated power (630hp actual vs 600hp claimed), excellent dual-clutch transmission, and impressive straight-line speed, it delivers on the M5 promise. However, the ride quality is quite stiff even in comfort mode, and the high price point makes it expensive. Still represents good value in the used market at around $50k. A compelling package that you 'get' once you drive it.

expertReviews.title: 2014 BMW M5 (F10) | Bruce Wayne by Day, Batman by Night
pros: Very fast with sub-4 second 0-60
Comfortable daily driver
Modern interior with analog gauges
Substantial difference between drive modes
Smooth and instant DCT shifts
More torque than predecessor due to twin turbo V8
cons: Heavier than previous generations at 4200-4300 lbs
expertReviews.verdict: The F10 M5 is an 'Autobahn missile' - extremely capable and comfortable for daily driving with impressive straight-line performance, but lacks the driver engagement and communication needed for spirited driving. Better suited for older drivers wanting practicality and speed rather than pure driving thrills. More capable than the E60 predecessor but less special in character.

expertReviews.title: In depth BMW F10 M5 Competition Review!
pros: Bang & Olufsen premium sound system with mechanical tweeters
Comprehensive luxury features including heated/cooled massaging seats
High-quality interior materials with carbon fiber accents and Alcantara headliner
Adaptive LED headlights and aggressive murdered-out appearance
Soft-close doors and hands-free trunk operation
Multiple drive modes with customizable settings
Spacious rear seating with privacy shades and individual climate controls
Premium leather throughout cabin with quality stitching
cons: Seat controls positioned inconveniently low on door panel
Hands-free trunk kick sensor less sensitive with aftermarket carbon diffuser
No traditional park gear - uses neutral with parking brake system
expertReviews.verdict: This 2016 BMW M5 Competition represents a well-specced example with premium options like Bang & Olufsen audio, carbon fiber interior trim, and comprehensive comfort features. The reviewer appreciates the traditional built-in infotainment over newer iPad-style systems and highlights the quality materials throughout. While noting some ergonomic quirks with control placement, the car demonstrates BMW's attention to luxury details in their flagship performance sedan.
